    "faq": {
      "title": "Frequently Asked Questions",
      "q1": "Why can't I delete a project that has actions?",
      "a1": "For data integrity, you must first delete all actions linked to the project.",
      "q2": "Does the project status update automatically?",
      "a2": "Action status is automatically determined when progress is 0% or 100%. For values in between, it is calculated based on threshold settings in the Settings page.",
      "q3": "Why can't I assign multiple tags?",
      "a3": "The multi-tag rule must be enabled from the Settings page. By default, only a single tag can be assigned.",
      "q4": "What does the review date mean?",
      "a4": "It indicates the next scheduled review date for the project. Overdue reviews are highlighted on the Home page.",
      "q5": "Which roles can access which pages?",
      "a5": "Page access permissions per role can be managed from the Security page. Admin has full system access.",
      "q6": "How do I change my language preference?",
      "a6": "You can select Turkish or English from the Profile page. Your preference is stored in the database.",
      "q7": "Can I export my data?",
      "a7": "You can export projects, actions, and other data in JSON, CSV, or XLSX format from the Data Management page."
